indicatorDescriptions.Labour force participation rate, %: Percentage of the population that engages actively in the labour market, either by working or looking for work.
indicatorDescriptions.Wage equality for similar work, 1-7 (bes: Response to the survey question, “In your country, for similar work, to what extent are wages for women equal to those of men?” (1 = not at all, significantly below those of men; 7 = fully, equal to those of men). The data is converted to a normalized 0-to-1 scale.
indicatorDescriptions.Estimated earned income, int'l $ 1,000: In the aggregate, the amount of income that women and men in the country receive, estimated using the proportion of working men and women, their relative wages, and overall Gross Domestic Product of the country in question.
indicatorDescriptions.Legislators, senior officials and manage: The ratio of women to men employed in senior roles, defined by the International Labour Organization as those who plan, direct, coordinate and evaluate the overall activities of enterprises, governments and other organizations, or of organizational units within them, and formulate and review their policies, laws, rules and regulations.
indicatorDescriptions.Professional and technical workers, %: The ratio of women to men employed in professional and technical roles, defined by the International Labour Organization as those who increase the existing stock of knowledge, apply scientific or artistic concepts and theories or those who perform technical and related tasks that require advanced knowledge and skill.
indicatorDescriptions.Literacy rate, %: Percentage of the population aged 15 and over with the ability to both read and write and make simple arithmetic calculations.
indicatorDescriptions.Enrolment in primary education, %: Percentage of children in the official primary school age range who are enrolled in either primary or secondary education.
indicatorDescriptions.Enrolment in secondary education, %: Percentage of children in the official age range for secondary education who are enrolled in secondary education.
indicatorDescriptions.Enrolment in tertiary education, %: Total enrolment in tertiary education, regardless of age, expressed as a percentage of the total population of the most recent five-year age cohort that has left secondary school.
indicatorDescriptions.Sex ratio at birth, %: The number of girls born in relation to every male birth. Biologically, this ratio should vary little and female births should be about 94.4% of male births. Divergance from this pattern points to practices that discriminate between female and male fetuses.
indicatorDescriptions.Healthy life expectancy, years: Average number of years that a person can expect to live in full health in a given country, calculated by taking into account years lived in less than full health due to disease and/or injury.
indicatorDescriptions.Women in parliament , %: Percentage of women who hold parliamentary seats. In instances when a parliamentary system is bicameral, the figure used is the one for the lower house.
indicatorDescriptions.Women in ministerial positions, %: Percentage of women holding ministerial portfolios. Some overlap between ministers and heads of state that also hold a ministerial portfolio may occur. Data is updated every two years.
indicatorDescriptions.Years with female/male head of state (la: The number of years in the past fifty year period for which a woman has held a post that is equivalent to head of state or head of government in the country.
